      outcomes: 'A documented governance backbone that codifies how the project (or property) treats people, partners, and power. The policies shape day-to-day decisions, set expectations for vendors and the value chain, and create reporting paths for misconduct. Together they make ethical conduct a baseline \u2014 not a value statement, but a governing instrument that\u2019s endorsed at the top, trained into the team, and reflected in how performance is rewarded.',
      whatItTakes: {
        intro: 'A site-specific Ethics & Fair Operating Practices Policy covering:',
        items: [
          'Bullying and harassment',
          'Gifts and hospitality',
          'Safety and health, including unauthorized weapons',
          'Money laundering',
          'Professional standards and conduct \u2014 including the obligation to dissent (any team member can flag a miscalculation regardless of hierarchy) and explicit support for minoritized groups and voices',
          'Anti-corruption, anti-bribery, fair competition',
          'Responsible political involvement (where applicable)',
          'Respect for property rights, including IP',
        ],
        sections: [
          {
            intro: 'A Supplier Code of Conduct covering:',
            items: [
              'Compliance with international and local law, trade restrictions, sanctions, environmental laws',
              'Anti-corruption, anti-bribery, anti-money laundering; transparency, accuracy, data security, privacy',
              'Globally recognized labor standards \u2014 no harassment or discrimination, fair compensation, prohibition of forced or child labor, freedom of association and collective bargaining where legal',
              'Local health and safety compliance',
              'Training and awareness for high-risk roles',
              'Open reporting channels for concerns and violations',
              'Vendors must commit to the code and extend similar standards to their supply chains',
            ],
